title: CDs being released Oct. 30
text:
CDs being released Oct. 30 October 25, 2015 Last updated: Sunday, October 25, 2015, 1:21 AM The Record TREY ANASTASIO 
* Trey Anastasio, "Paper Wheels" (Rubber Jungle/ATO) — The 10th solo album from the Phish frontman. 
* Bryan Adams, "Get Up!" (UMe) — Produced by ELO frontman Jeff Lynne and co-written with his long-time collaborator Jim Vallance, the album features nine new songs plus four acoustic versions. 
* Def Leppard, "Def Leppard" (Mailboat) — The band’s first studio album since "Songs from the Sparkle Lounge" (2008), marking the longest gap between two studio albums in their career. 
* Steve Martin and Edie Brickell, "So Familiar" (Rounder) — Grammy-winning bluegrass duo returns with Martin on banjo and Brickell singing.
